<TITLE> Teenage boy murdered in Leicester </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 London, Jan 1 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A 16-year-old boy has been found dead on a Leicester street following a report of an assault, police said on Tuesday. Officers were called shortly after 5 a.m. to Fosse Road South where the teenager was pronounced dead. Police said they were treating his death as murder and had arrested three people, a 14-year-old boy, a 15-year-old girl and a 31-year-old woman, all from Leicester. The area remains cordoned off while forensic officers examine the scene. "We are in the very early stages of the investigation and are trying to piece together exactly what happened," said Detective Chief Inspector Phil Smith
